notesStmt.note: This late medieval German prayer book is an example of a highly personal devotional item. It was originally made ca. 1440 for Leonhard von Laymingen, bishop of Passau (fl. 1423-1451). The text primarily features a series of prayers to various saints as well as prayers for travelings. Many illuminations and some text pages have been excised, but the book is nonetheless extensively decorated. The prayer book's illuminations consist of thirty miniatures and four historiated initials that complement the text, usually with illustrations of saints. Bishop von Laymingen appears in his prayer book several times kneeling before the saint to which that particular prayer is dedicated. Additionally, the Laymingen coat of arms appears twenty times throughout the book.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Latin.

msItem.title: Prayer book of Leonhard von Laymingen of Passau
msItem.note: The majority of the text is prayers to various saints, also included is St. Bernard's Meditation on the Salve Regina; many leaves excised and there appear to be several whole prayers missing; two added later inscriptions: a seventeenth century cursive (fol. 1r) and a late fifteenth century cursive (fol. 181v).

binding.p: Austrian binding ca. 1600, brown leather over beech boards; blind-stamped and tooled Crucifixion scene, floral and fleur-de-lys decoration; impressions and brass rivets of former clasps remain

history.provenance: Made for Leonhard von Laymingen, bishop of Passau (fl. 1423-1451)
Don Marcello Massarenti (1817-1905) collection, Rome, no. 475 (stickers on outer and inner upper board and paper pastedown inside lower board)
Henry Walters, Baltimore, 1902, purchased from Massarenti collection
history.acquisition: Walters Art Museum, 1931, by Henry Walters' bequest
